How I installed MongoDB Community Version:

1. Run **sudo apt update**  
   1. This updates your ubuntu/wsl to the latest version

![][image1]

2. Run **cat /etc/lsb-release**  
   1. This checks what ubuntu release host is using  
   2. Note: it must be 64-bit LTS on x86\_64 architecture  
   3. You should end up with   
      1. 24.04 LTS (“Noble”)  
      2. 22.04 LTS (“Jammy”)  
      3. 20.04 LTS (“Focal”)

![][image2]  
So as you can see here, I have jammy

3. Run **sudo apt-get install gnupg curl**  
   1. These are some other things we need in order to have mongodb on our computer   
   2. If you happen to run into an issue, check the mongodb documentation [here](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/#std-label-install-mdb-community-ubuntu)

![][image3]

4. Based on your Ubuntu Release, you will run one of the following commands:  
   1. Noble   
      1. **echo "deb \[ arch=amd64,arm64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-8.0.gpg \] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu noble/mongodb-org/8.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-8.0.list**  
   2. Jammy  
      1. **echo "deb \[ arch=amd64,arm64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-8.0.gpg \] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu jammy/mongodb-org/8.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-8.0.list**  
   3. Focal  
      1. **echo "deb \[ arch=amd64,arm64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-8.0.gpg \] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu focal/mongodb-org/8.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-8.0.list**

5. Run **sudo apt-get install \-y mongodb-org**

**below is for checking other things like starting and stopping mongodb from running**

6. Run **sudo systemctl start mongod**  
   1. This starts mongodb  
   2. If you run into errors, check [here](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/#std-label-install-mdb-community-ubuntu)  
7. Run sudo systemctl stop mongod  
   1. This stops mongodb

8. Run **mongosh**  
   1. This starts it
